column4: Tesla reports fourth-quarter loss  misses sales targets
column5: DETROIT Tesla Motors Inc  missed sales targets and racked up a fourth-quarter loss of $107.6 million as the luxury electric car maker struggled with production and delivery issues on several fronts.

column4: UPDATE 1-Tesla reports 4th-quarter loss  misses sales targets
column5: DETROIT  Feb 11 Tesla Motors Inc missed sales targets and racked up a fourth-quarter loss of $107.6 million as the luxury electric car maker struggled with production and delivery issues on several fronts.
DETROIT  Feb 11 Tesla Motors Inc on Wednesday reported a fourth-quarter loss of $107.6 million  or 86 cents per share  compared with a year-ago loss of $16.3 million  or 13 cents per share.

column4: Exclusive: Tesla CEO threatens firings after dismal China sales - sources
column5: PARIS/DETROIT Tesla Motors Inc  Chief Executive Elon Musk is prepared to fire overseas executives  people with knowledge of the matter said  after weak Chinese sales of the company's luxury electric cars cast doubt on his ambitious global expansion plans. | Video

column4: Nvidia's fiscal fourth-quarter results beat estimates  stock rises
column5: SAN FRANCISCO Nvidia Corp  on Wednesday posted higher quarterly results that beat Wall Street expectations  sending its shares higher as the graphics chipmaker sought to sharpen its focus on high-end automobiles.

column4: UPDATE 2-Nvidia's fiscal 4th-quarter results beat estimates  stock rises
column5: SAN FRANCISCO  Feb 11 Nvidia Corp on Wednesday posted higher quarterly results that beat Wall Street expectations  sending its shares higher as the graphics chipmaker sought to sharpen its focus on high-end automobiles.
SAN FRANCISCO  Feb 11 Nvidia Corp on Wednesday posted higher fiscal fourth-quarter revenue that beat Wall Street's expectations as the graphics chipmaker increased its focus on high-end automobiles.

column4: China stocks up on expectations of more policy easing  Hong Kong lags
column5: SHANGHAI  Feb 11 China shares rose for a third straight day on Wednesday after the central bank vowed to support economic growth  but investors were reluctant to chase stocks too high on concerns that the rebound was due to technical factors and may be short-lived.

column4: Robust switching sales power strong quarter for Cisco
column5: Network equipment maker Cisco Systems Inc  reported stronger-than-expected quarterly revenue and profit as demand for switching equipment and routers helped to make up for weak spending by the company's traditional telecom customers. | Video

column4: UPDATE 3-Robust switching sales power strong quarter for Cisco
column5: * Shares rise 5.6 pct in extended trading   (Adds analyst comments)

column4: Cisco revenue rises 7 pct on higher demand for switches  routers
column5: Feb 11 Network equipment maker Cisco Systems Inc CSCO.O reported a 7 percent rise in quarterly revenue  helped by higher demand for switching equipment and routers.
